RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Civilian
<hw>Ci*vil"ian</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Civil</er>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One skilled in the civil
law.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Ancient <qex>civilians</qex> and writers upon government.</q>
<rj><qau>Swift.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A student of the civil law at a university or
college.</def> <rj><au>R. Graves.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>One whose pursuits are those of civil life, not
military or clerical.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Civilist</ent>⟦br⟧
